# TASK_PACKET

Task ID
CRUSHR-SCRUB-02

Title
Reject duplicate logical archive paths at pack time and fail closed before archive emission

Role
BUILDER

Objective
Eliminate silent logical-path collisions during packing.

This packet addresses a real correctness defect identified in hostile review:

- `crushr-pack` currently derives logical paths for standalone inputs using basenames
- different source files can collapse onto the same archive path
- the pack path does not reject duplicates before writing archive structures

For an integrity-first archive format, silently allowing duplicate logical paths is unacceptable.

This packet must make duplicate logical path collisions a deterministic hard failure.

